description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for enthusiastic and innovative Registered Mental Health Nurses (RMNs) to work within our female and male PICU wards at Tower Hamlets Mental Health Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for skilled and passionate Band 5 Nurses, both experienced and newly qualified, to join our dedicated teams on Milhabour and Rosebank Wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, you will need to be enthusiastic, forward thinking and have a keen interest in working with patients being nursed in an psychiatric intensive care unit. You will be working within a supportive multidisciplinary team, caring for patients with a wide range of needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our care and treatment programmes are underpinned by principles of recovery and social inclusion and much of our work is co-produced with patients. You will help to ensure that the people we care for always have a strong voice. If you are committed to providing outstanding patient care with a sound knowledge of best practise, this is the opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
